However, the boys can also sit in alternating places with the girls; there are two ways to alternate boys with girls (or vice versa). If the boys are sitting at the ends of the row, there will always be a girl between each pair of boys. If the boys are not at the ends, there will be a boy in the middle of the row, so we have another $8!$ arrangements to account for. Therefore, we add the two different arrangements for boys alternating with girls and the arrangements with boys sitting in an alternating place, for a total of $2 \times (8!+8!) = \boxed{1280 \times 8!}$.


